comments.body:
Hi [~yuanbo], thanks for addressing the issue. I see that Guice itself [fixed it|https://github.com/google/guice/pull/860/files] using {{java.net.URI#getPath}}. Let us use it here so the behavior is consistent with newer Guice.

I suggest we use:

{code}
decodedPathInfo = URI.create(pathInfo).getPath();
{code}

Minor thing, since we have this catch clause, can we add the pathInfo value and stack trace to the log message:
{code}
}  catch (URISyntaxException ex) {
  LOG.error(pathInfo + ": Failed to decode path.", ex);
}
{code}
